.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-CLOSE" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-close \- close a Lightning payment channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-close
.I channel_id
.RB [ --force ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Cooperatively closes a channel via
.BR lightning-cli (1)
.BR close .
With
.B --force
the channel is unilaterally closed (sweep to chain).
.PP
Returns JSON
.B {"txid":"...","type":"mutual"|"unilateral"}
on success.
.TP
.B --force
Force-close (unilateral); use only when the peer is unresponsive.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Close initiated.
.TP
.B 5
Close failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-open (1),
.BR lightning-peer-disconnect (1)
